article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 67, McNeese State 53
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) -- Matt Kingsley and Will Johnson scored 12 points each for Stephen F. Austin, which beat McNeese State 67-53 on Saturday. SFA (11-5, 4-0 Southland) hit 65 percent of its first-half shots for a 34-22 halftime lead. McNeese got 16 of the next 20 points to tie the score at 38-38 when Jarvis Bradley hit a slam dunk with 12:37 left. He finished with 10 points for the Cowboys. The score was tied again at 40, but SFA got the next seven points, four of them on free throws by Kingsley, and led the rest of the game. Josh Alexander added 10 for the Lumberjacks. Troy Aaron led the Cowboys (6-11, 1-2) with 13 points and John Ford had 10.
